body.description: ACDelco AA super Alkaline batteries are equipped with advanced technology you can count on. ACDelco Alkaline batteries perform better than the competition in high-drain and super high-drain devices, and they provide consistent discharge performance. ACDelco Alkaline batteries are designed for long shelf-life with stainless steel pre-coating that prevents leakage and advanced ingredient formulation that helps maintain power over time. This reclosable storage pack includes 40 AA batteries great for a variety of household devices, including clocks, remote controls, and toys. The 1.5-Volt batteries contain no mercury or cadmium, making them a smart choice for your family and for the environment. A trusted national brand, ACDelco offers a wide variety of batteries you can count on, including Alkaline batteries, lithium coin cell batteries, rechargeable batteries, and car batteries.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lots of long lasting batteries
reviews.reviewText: Usually when I need batteries I think of Duracell or some brand name that cost up to $2 dollars a single battery, but when I saw 100 of these batteries for such a low price I immediately thought "they must either have a low battery life or be defective" and boy was I surprised to see just how effective they are; every single battery works, none come dead or with half a charge, they aren't as strong as the big brand I'm not going to lie there, but they last about 80% as much as the big brand's. Plus with 100 at such a low price I still came out on top; Toys, remote controllers, Xbox controllers, new and old tech. I was able to power all of them up and still have enough to share with my neighbors. Over all a good buy for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent value and quality
reviews.reviewText: I found the AC Delco brand of alkaline batteries on Amazon a few years ago and now it’s the only brand I purchase. I use to buy Duracell batteries at Costco but these are a much better value. They are the least expensive batteries I have been able to find and they last just as long as the other name brand batteries. They say you can store them for up to 15 years and I don’t mind buying them in bulk. I always seem to use more batteries than I think I will and I like to have extras on hand. They come is sturdy boxes with the battery size printed on them so they are easy to store.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Fan of ACDelco 60-Count AA Batteries
reviews.reviewText: ACDelco batteries seem to last a long time. I've used other brands in the past, but these for the price they were at the time, were a very good deal, and so far they are performing well. They also come in a very nice plastic container that keeps them stored nicely and can easily be seen what you need without having to open a box to find the right batteries.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for Toddler toys!!!
reviews.reviewText: These budget-friendly batteries are a practical choice for toddler toys that frequently require replacements. While they may not boast the longevity of pricier brands, their affordability makes them a smart option for households with energetic little ones and a constant need for battery-powered toys. The cost-effectiveness outweighs the shorter lifespan, providing a convenient solution for keeping the fun going without breaking the bank. If you're looking for a reliable and economical power source for your toddler's toys, these batteries are a worthwhile consideration.
